# Gateway - Trivy image-scan accepted-risks list.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Each CVE below was CRITICAL+fixable when Trivy flagged it, but the fix
# lives in an UPSTREAM image we don't build. We accept the risk until the
# upstream maintainer publishes a rebuild, or we bump the tag.
#
# REVIEW CADENCE: first Monday of every quarter. When reviewing:
#   1. Re-run `gh run rerun <latest> --failed` to refresh the list.
#   2. For each CVE still listed, check whether upstream has published a
#      new image tag or an advisory marking it non-exploitable in this
#      deployment (e.g. SSH code paths in Loki we never reach).
#   3. Delete anything that's been fixed; CI will tell you if a new one
#      appears that isn't listed.
# LAST REVIEWED: 2026-04-21 (n8n bumped 1.28.0 → 2.18.0; Redpanda + Grafana new CVEs added)
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Dockerfile misconfigurations ---
# Applies repo-wide; if we ever add another Dockerfile that SHOULD be non-
# root, remove this line and scope the exception via .trivyignore.yaml.
# Currently relevant only to admin-ui/backend/Dockerfile which intentionally
# runs as root to:
#   (a) write to the bind-mounted .env regardless of host file ownership
#   (b) speak to /var/run/docker.sock for the restart endpoint
# The admin-ui service is profile-gated (--profile admin) and binds only to
# 127.0.0.1:7070, so the blast radius of rootful execution is a single-host
# operator who's already chosen to enable it.
AVD-DS-0002

# --- Go stdlib / toolchain (present in every Go-based image) ---
# Loki, Promtail, Prometheus, Alertmanager, Grafana, Redpanda, etc. ship
# statically-linked Go binaries whose stdlib version is fixed at image
# build time. Each of these is resolved by a rebuild with Go >=1.22.4 / 1.24.13.
CVE-2024-24790        # net/netip: IPv4-in-IPv6 Is* misbehavior
CVE-2025-68121        # crypto/tls: cert validation during session resumption
CVE-2026-27497        # stdlib
CVE-2026-27498        # stdlib
CVE-2026-28292        # stdlib
CVE-2026-33660        # stdlib
CVE-2026-33696        # stdlib
CVE-2026-33863        # stdlib
CVE-2026-33864        # stdlib

# --- golang.org/x/crypto ---
# SSH server-side bug in PublicKeyCallback. Gateway containers do not
# expose SSH server paths using this library, but the binary still embeds it.
CVE-2024-45337

# --- google.golang.org/grpc ---
# HTTP/2 path-validation authz bypass in grpc-go authz middleware. We don't
# use grpc-go authz middleware directly; upstream services that embed it
# (e.g. Loki, Promtail) will fix on rebuild.
CVE-2026-33186

# --- github.com/docker/docker (moby) ---
# Auth regression; only reachable through Docker API. The Go binary inside
# Promtail embeds this transitively. Promtail does not expose a docker
# socket server - it only reads /var/run/docker.sock as a client.
CVE-2024-41110

# --- Debian base images (postgres-exporter path, promtail) ---
# Krb5 + libsasl2 + OpenSSL chain. We don't use GSSAPI / Kerberos auth to
# Postgres or Redis in this stack. OpenSSL issues are primarily TLS server
# paths; our TLS terminates at Kong, which uses its own OpenSSL build.
CVE-2024-37371        # krb5 GSS message token
CVE-2023-24538        # older Go text/template (promtail)
CVE-2023-24540        # older Go text/template (promtail)
CVE-2023-36665        # (promtail)

# --- go-git (Redpanda Console) ---
# CVE-2025-21613: argument injection via URL in go-git; fixed in go-git 5.13.0.
# Redpanda Console (redpandadata/console) embeds go-git as a transitive dep but
# does not expose any UI path that invokes git clone/fetch with user-controlled
# URLs. Console is bound to 127.0.0.1:8080, reachable only via SSH tunnel.
CVE-2025-21613         # go-git arg injection; fixed in 5.13.0; console doesn't use git URLs

# --- OpenSSL (Redpanda + other Alpine/Debian base images) ---
# CVE-2025-15467: OpenSSL RCE fixed in 3.0.18 / 3.3.6. The upstream images
# (Redpanda v24.1.7, and any Debian-based images still on older OpenSSL) have
# not been rebuilt against the patched release yet. Risk-mitigated: TLS
# terminates at Kong which uses its own OpenSSL build; Redpanda listens only
# on internal Docker networks and is not reachable from the public internet.
CVE-2025-15467         # openssl RCE; fixed in 3.0.18+/3.3.6+; upstream rebuild pending

# --- Grafana plugin SDK ---
# CVE-2024-8986: Information leakage in grafana-plugin-sdk-go; fixed in
# sdk 0.250.0 / Grafana 11.x+. We pin Grafana 10.4.1 for dashboard
# compatibility; the vulnerability is in plugin RPC paths not exercised by
# our provisioned dashboards. Grafana is loopback-only (127.0.0.1:3002).
CVE-2024-8986          # grafana-plugin-sdk-go info leak; fixed in sdk 0.250.0 / Grafana 11+

# --- Node.js / npm (n8n image) ---
# n8nio/n8n:2.18.0 — one remaining CRITICAL in protobufjs (transitive dep
# bundled by n8n; no upgrade path until n8n bumps protobufjs to >=7.5.5/8.0.1).
# Risk-mitigated: n8n is loopback-only behind Kong auth; protobufjs is used
# for gRPC serialization, not exposed via any public code path in our workflows.
CVE-2026-41242         # protobufjs arbitrary code execution; fixed in 7.5.5 / 8.0.1
